<span id="freeTextContainer9861590379196082321">This book answers questions I had after reading book one. The writing is superb... Kesi starts off young and learning about boys (human boys in this case) and about her place in life. As she grows and matures, so does the writing style. So real you would think these scrolls once existed for real. Hmm, did they? An EXCELLENT read for anyone, whether or not you like vampires.</span>

          </span>
