<div id="review_1883713133" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1883713133" />
    <a title="Sussu Leclerc" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23002092-sussu-leclerc"><img alt="Sussu Leclerc" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1402249897p2/23002092.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1883713133?book_show_action=true">Jan 18, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sussu Leclerc" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sussu Leclerc" href="/user/show/23002092-sussu-leclerc">Sussu Leclerc</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1883713133" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1339524016211066979">This is an interesting story that shows vampires through a different point of view. The heroine of this novella comes to terms with who she is. She discovers with horror and despair that she can burn under the sun, that she can command people&apos;s feelings and they might not truly love her, that she cannot have children and has to marry a man with warts to fit the family&apos;s expectations. The tale explains how vampires, inside their own world, can be chained to conventions and hierarchy. This story i</span>
  <span id="freeText1339524016211066979" style="display:none">This is an interesting story that shows vampires through a different point of view. The heroine of this novella comes to terms with who she is. She discovers with horror and despair that she can burn under the sun, that she can command people's feelings and they might not truly love her, that she cannot have children and has to marry a man with warts to fit the family's expectations. The tale explains how vampires, inside their own world, can be chained to conventions and hierarchy. This story is summarized and it is a series of entries in a journal. Despite being telling, the story will hook you and will not let go. Much more than a love story as it first appears, it is the story of an unusual coming of age. Mesmerizing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1339524016211066979" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


